              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(a figurative extension of meaning of {L:ἀποθνῄσκω&lt;SDBG:ἀποθνῄσκω:000000&gt;}[a] ‘to die,’ {D:23.99}) to be unable to respond or react to any impulse or desire</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to be dead to</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to not respond to</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to have no part in</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages it is extremely difficult to speak of ‘dying to sin.’ In some instances one can preserve the figurative meaning by an expression such as ‘to be like dead as far as desiring to sin’ or ‘to be like a corpse as far as temptations to sin are concerned.’</Comments>
